article.description: Reid Sinnett threw five touchdown passes and ran for another score to lead San Diego in a 42-17 rout of Valparaiso on Saturday.
article.headline: Sinnett has 6 TDs, leads San Diego in 42-17 rout of Valpo
article.linkText: Sinnett has 6 TDs, leads San Diego in 42-17 rout of Valpo
article.story: SAN DIEGO -- Reid Sinnett threw five touchdown passes and ran for another score to lead San Diego in a 42-17 rout of Valparaiso on Saturday. Sinnett was 21-of-31 passing for 271 yards and added 63 yards rushing. Michael Bandy had three touchdown catches and finished with eight receptions for 171 yards for the Toreros (4-2, 3-0 Pioneer League). Alex Spadone caught five passes, two for scores. San Diego forced a season-high four turnovers with two interceptions and two fumble recoveries. The Toreros jumped out to a 28-3 halftime lead. Chris Duncan had two touchdown runs in the third quarter for Valparaiso (0-7, 0-3). Duncan was 16 of 26 for 182 yards passing and added 32 yards rushing. San Diego has scored 30 or more points in nine straight games dating to last season.
